  ARRAY['Ultimate Rewards: 14+ airline & hotel partners','Sapphire Reserve: 3× travel + dining, Priority Pass','Ink Business lineup for freelancers and SMBs']::text[],
  ARRAY['Ultimate Rewards transfers to 14+ airlines & hotels at strong value (often 2¢+ per point)','Sapphire Reserve earns 3× on all travel and dining worldwide, includes Priority Pass lounge access and a $300 travel credit','Ink Business cards (Cash, Preferred, Unlimited) cover most small-business spending categories at 3–5×']::text[],
  ARRAY['5/24 rule: 5+ new cards in 24 months = automatic rejection at Chase','Needs good to excellent credit (700+ recommended) — no path for fair or bad credit','No secured or student card in the lineup']::text[],
  '{"cost":8.8,"features":9.6,"ux":9.2,"support":8.4}'::jsonb,
  'The strongest rewards ecosystem in the US credit card market',
  'Chase dominates the US credit card market — the Ultimate Rewards ecosystem transfers to 14+ airline and hotel partners at strong value (often 2¢+ per point), and the Sapphire Preferred is the most-recommended starter travel card across every major comparison site. The Ink Business lineup (Cash, Preferred, Unlimited) covers most small-business spending at 3–5× with no annual fee on two of the three. The one hard constraint is the 5/24 rule: Chase automatically denies most applicants who have opened five or more credit cards across any issuer in the past 24 months, so Chase cards are best applied for before exploring other issuers.',
  false, NULL, 'https://creditcards.chase.com/', true, 'Best for: Travel rewards & business cards', 1,
  'https://creditcards.chase.com/', DATE '2026-07-05', true
),
