  ARRAY['Membership Rewards transfer to 21 airline and hotel partners, including ANA, Air France/KLM, and Singapore Airlines — among the widest transfer networks in the US','The Platinum card includes Centurion, Delta Sky Club, and Priority Pass lounge access covering 800+ global lounges','Best-in-class purchase protection and extended warranty on all Amex cards, regardless of annual fee']::text[],
  ARRAY['Not accepted at ~1–4% of US merchants — carry a Visa or Mastercard as a backup internationally','$695 Platinum annual fee — requires actively using travel credits, Uber Cash, and other perks to break even','No secured or student cards — approval is selective, typically requiring good-to-excellent credit']::text[],
  '{"cost":7.8,"features":9.8,"ux":9.4,"support":8.6}'::jsonb,
  'The best premium travel and business card issuer in the US',
  'American Express leads in premium travel and business cards — the Platinum''s 800+ lounge network and the Gold''s 4× dining/groceries have no close rivals, and Membership Rewards transfers to 21 partners including ANA, Air France/KLM, and Singapore Airlines at up to 1.4–2¢+ per point. The honest caveats: the Platinum''s $695 annual fee requires actively using travel credits and Uber Cash to break even, and Amex acceptance — while over 99% domestically — can lag Visa and Mastercard in certain international markets, so carrying a backup card is advisable when traveling abroad.',
