  'official', 'high',
  '[]'::jsonb,
  ARRAY['Double Cash: 2% on everything, no tracking','Longest 0% APR for balance transfers (21 mo)','Strata Premier: 3× travel, groceries, dining']::text[],
  ARRAY['Double Cash earns 2% on every purchase (1% when you buy, 1% when you pay) — the simplest flat-rate cash back card in the US market, no annual fee','Longest 0% APR promotional period for balance transfers in this comparison: up to 21 months with a 3–5% transfer fee — the default pick for paying down existing debt interest-free','Strata Premier earns 3× on travel, hotels, grocery stores, and restaurants, with ThankYou points transferable to American Airlines, Air France/KLM, and 15+ other partners']::text[],
  ARRAY['ThankYou Points transfer network has fewer premium airline partners than Chase Ultimate Rewards or Amex Membership Rewards','App and online banking experience rated below Chase, Amex, and Capital One in user reviews','No secured card in the current lineup — applicants below ~670 FICO should look elsewhere']::text[],
  '{"cost":9.0,"features":8.2,"ux":7.8,"support":7.4}'::jsonb,
  'The best balance transfer issuer and the simplest flat-rate cash back card',
  'Citi''s Double Cash card (2% back on everything — 1% when you buy, 1% when you pay) remains the simplest flat-rate cash back card in the US market with no annual fee, and the Strata Premier (3× travel, hotels, groceries, restaurants) earns ThankYou Points transferable to American Airlines, Air France/KLM, Wyndham, and 15 others. Citi''s biggest strength is its balance transfer products: 0% APR promotional periods up to 21 months with a 3–5% transfer fee are the longest in this comparison, making Citi the default pick for carrying an existing balance interest-free while paying it down.',
  false, NULL, 'https://www.citi.com/credit-cards/credit-card-offers/', false, 'Best for: Balance transfers & cash back', 4,
  'https://www.citi.com/credit-cards/credit-card-offers/', DATE '2026-07-05', true
