  ARRAY['Cashback Match automatically doubles every dollar of cash back earned in year 1 — no cap, no conditions, no enrollment needed','Zero annual fee on every Discover card, including the Secured it — no other major issuer is $0 across the entire portfolio','The Secured it card auto-graduates to an unsecured card with a credit limit increase after approximately seven months of on-time payments']::text[],
  ARRAY['Fewer international merchants than Visa or Mastercard — acceptance gaps at some overseas locations','Rotating 5% categories (up to $1,500/quarter) require quarterly opt-in activation — easy to forget','Now a Capital One subsidiary (merger May 2025) — brand continues for now, but long-term trajectory is uncertain']::text[],
  '{"cost":9.4,"features":7.8,"ux":8.6,"support":8.0}'::jsonb,
  'The best issuer for beginners, students, and credit builders',
  'Discover builds its value proposition around the first-year Cashback Match — every dollar of cash back earned in year 1 is doubled automatically, with no spending caps. All Discover cards charge zero annual fee, zero foreign transaction fees, and carry no penalty APR (rates don''t spike if you miss a payment). The Secured it card is the strongest mainstream option for credit-building: it auto-graduates to an unsecured card after approximately seven months of on-time payments. Important context: Discover is now a Capital One subsidiary (merger closed May 2025) — it continues to operate as a separate brand, but the long-term trajectory is uncertain.',
  false, NULL, 'https://www.discover.com/credit-cards/', false, 'Best for: Students & credit beginners', 5,
  'https://www.discover.com/credit-cards/', DATE '2026-07-05', true
