  'official', 'medium',
  '[]'::jsonb,
  ARRAY['Cash+: choose your own 5% categories quarterly','Altitude Reserve: 3× on Apple Pay/mobile wallet','No foreign transaction fees on flagship cards']::text[],
  ARRAY['Cash+ Visa lets cardholders choose their own 5% categories (gas, utilities, fast food, TV/internet, and more) updated quarterly, plus a 2% everyday category — the most flexible category cash back structure in the US','Altitude Reserve earns 3× on all purchases made via mobile wallet (Apple Pay, Google Pay, Samsung Pay) — the best card for heavy contactless spenders','No foreign transaction fees on the Altitude Connect and Altitude Reserve travel cards']::text[],
  ARRAY['Less brand recognition than the top-5 issuers — limited branch footprint outside core US markets','Altitude Reserve ($400/year) requires excellent credit and lags Chase Sapphire Reserve in lounge access and transfer partners','Rewards ecosystem is smaller than Chase, Amex, or Capital One — fewer redemption options for points']::text[],
  '{"cost":8.4,"features":8.2,"ux":8.2,"support":7.6}'::jsonb,
  'The best issuer for category optimizers and mobile-wallet users',
  'U.S. Bank''s niche is category optimization — the Cash+ Visa lets cardholders choose their own 5% category (gas, utilities, fast food, TV/internet, and more) and a 2% everyday category, updated quarterly, with no annual fee. The Altitude Reserve targets frequent mobile-wallet users with 3× on Apple Pay, Google Pay, and Samsung Pay purchases. The Altitude Connect ($95/year) bridges the gap with 4× travel and grocery, Priority Pass (4 visits/year), and TSA PreCheck credit. The tradeoff: U.S. Bank has fewer branches than JPMorgan Chase or Bank of America, and the rewards ecosystem is smaller.',
  false, NULL, 'https://www.usbank.com/credit-cards.html', false, 'Best for: Category maximizers', 8,
  'https://www.usbank.com/credit-cards.html', DATE '2026-07-05', true
